name: Get Wi-Fi Signal Strength
description: Informs users who are not connected to a corporate network and have a connection strength lower than the threshold specified that their connection is not good for optimal work. In addition gets feedback on the usefulness of the campaign.

inputs.description: Comma-separated list of SSIDs which are defined as corporate. It can be empty
inputs.name: CorporateNetworks

inputs.description: Minimum signal quality percentage to consider the current wireless network as good (0 to 100)
inputs.name: AcceptableSignalQuality

inputs.description: Minimum signal quality percentage to consider nearby networks to be competing with the current wireless network (0 to 100)
inputs.name: NearbyNetworksAcceptableSignalQuality

inputs.description: Maximum signal percentage difference between the current wireless network and the available networks to consider them as competing (0 to 100)
inputs.name: NearbyNetworksMaximumSignalDifference

inputs.description: Number of times (1 to 200) the signal has to be under the acceptable threshold during current day to notify the user via a campaign
inputs.name: AlertUserAfterBadSignals

inputs.description: If set to 'true' BSSID data for Wifi networks will not be displayed 'ANONYMIZED' will be shown
inputs.name: AnonymizeBSSID

inputs.description: Campaign to show to recommend to get closer to the router. Use an empty GUID (00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000) to avoid campaign
inputs.name: CampaignId

outputs.description: If the device is connected to a wireless network categorized as corporate
outputs.name: ConnectedToCorporateWiFi

outputs.description: Signal quality percentage as presented by Windows
outputs.name: WiFiSignalQuality

outputs.description: Wi-Fi signal quality average during the current day
outputs.name: WiFiSignalQualityAverage

outputs.description: Number of times the Wi-Fi signal quality was below the acceptable signal threshold during the current day
outputs.name: BadSignalCount

outputs.description: Percentage of time the Wi-Fi signal quality was below the acceptable signal threshold during the current day
outputs.name: BadSignalPercentage

outputs.description: Speed of the connected wireless network in Mbps (Megabits per second)
outputs.name: WiFiSpeed

outputs.description: Radio type used by the device's adapter connected to the active wireless network
outputs.name: WiFiRadioType

outputs.description: Channel used by the active wireless network
outputs.name: WiFiChannel

outputs.description: If there is noise caused by competing networks using the same channel as the active wireless network
outputs.name: CoChannelCongestion

outputs.description: Details of the co-channel competing networks if there are any. The list is in CSV format
outputs.name: CoChannelsList

outputs.description: If there is noise caused by competing networks using adjacent channels with respect to the active wireless network
outputs.name: AdjacentChannelsCongestion

outputs.description: Details of the adjacent competing networks if there are any. The list is in CSV format
outputs.name: AdjacentChannelsList

outputs.description: If the user answered to the campaign affirmatively
outputs.name: UserConsideredTipAsUseful
